{"id":878,"date":"2022-05-24T08:26:00","date_gmt":"2022-05-24T05:26:00","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/?p=878"},"modified":"2022-05-22T08:42:11","modified_gmt":"2022-05-22T05:42:11","slug":"open-an-account-for-your-employees-and-clients","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/open-an-account-for-your-employees-and-clients\/","title":{"rendered":"Easy Opening of an Account for Your Employees, Clients and Business"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>About eighty per cent of businesses have different bank accounts for personal and business purposes. A separate account will enable your entity to organize its accounting records, avoid overspending, and accurately file taxes.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ideally, you may opt to open a general checking or savings, payroll, or business tax account integrated or linked to your employees or clients. Despite all these, there are standard procedures to be followed when you\u2019re seeking accounts that incorporate such services.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Key steps of opening an account include making your choice and approaching the bank, plus preparing the required documents. You can open employee or client accounts online or in person, after which you\u2019ll verify that the set-up is in order. In this article, let\u2019s explore how to easily open an account for your employees, clients or business.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_45 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-grey ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"ez-toc-pull-right ez-toc-btn ez-toc-btn-xs ez-toc-btn-default ez-toc-toggle\" area-label=\"ez-toc-toggle-icon-1\"><label for=\"item-673d661980b95\" aria-label=\"Table of Content\"><span style=\"display: flex;align-items: center;width: 35px;height: 30px;justify-content: center;direction:ltr;\"><svg style=\"fill: #999;color:#999\" xmlns=\"ht